    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Tsnungwe, a federally-recognized tribe indigenous to parts of what is today Trinity and Humboldt counties, California; specifically, the Tsnungwe are indigenous to areas along the South Fork Trinity River, Willow Creek, Salyer, Burnt Ranch, and New River. The name of the tribe in their local language is tse:ningxwe. "tse:ning" refers to Ironside Mountain. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
